Monitor Linux servers CPU/Memory/Load Average
1. CPU Usage
top -b -n1 | grep "Cpu(s)"
Shows user/system/idle CPU percentages.

Alternative:

mpstat -P ALL 1 1

2. Memory Usage
free -h
Displays total, used, and available memory.

Alternative:

vmstat -s

3. Load Average
uptime
or
cat /proc/loadavg
Shows 1, 5, 15 minute load averages.

4. Combined View
top
or
htop
htop (install separately) gives a real-time, colored view with CPU/memory bars.

